title: 'Spanish CCN-CERT ENS Server'

description: |-
  This profile contains configuration for a RHEL7/CentOS7 server to comply with requirements defined in the spanish "Esquema Nacional de Seguridad" (ENS).

  These requirements are defined in the guide CCN-STIC-619. A copy of this document can be found in the following URL:

  https://www.ccn-cert.cni.es/pdf/guias/series-ccn-stic/guias-de-acceso-publico-ccn-stic/3674-ccn-stic-619-implementacion-de-seguridad-sobre-centos7/file.html

  In this profile we don't apply some of the defined requirements in CCN-STIC-619. These are the applied changes, and the reason to change it:

  * We don't disable ALL ICMP:  It's not a risk
  * dhfldkashgkljasdfg: difhylasdf


  For questions, info, coments, patches, etc, contact me:
  Kuko Armas &lt;kuko@canarytek.com&gt;

